Breaking my 3 day fast with this beautiful and delicious meal. Yeah you read that right. 3 days! The last thing I ate was a bite of sausage on Monday morning. 
â€¢
I intermittently fast most of the time. I donâ€™t usually have my first meal until around noon and my last meal is usually around 6-7. This is easy. 
â€¢
Every once in a while I will do a 24 hour fast. That was the plan this time. But for some reason after the first day I said to myself â€œletâ€™s see if we can do 2 daysâ€. I felt pretty good after 2 and said â€œletâ€™s do 3â€.
â€¢
In all honesty it was a lot easier than I expected. The worst part was being around food and choosing not to eat it. I didnâ€™t feel bad. I still had plenty of energy and my mood was great. I was starting to feel some effects last night. But nothing major. 
â€¢
With all that being said Iâ€™m not some crazy person. Iâ€™ve done some research on this. There are some great benefits to doing this. It is great at detoxing your body. It really helps your immune system. Not to mention the mental strength it requires to do this on purpose. 
â€¢
Iâ€™m not advocating that everyone do this. There are plenty of people that should not do this. But if you know what youâ€™re doing and you listen to your body you can accomplish great things. 
â€¢

â„ï¸ ğŸ˜´ It's winter. An for many of us, retaining a big yawn in chilly weather is almost a feat! â 
â 
â„ï¸â˜ƒï¸ In this cold weather, even dogs yawn! â 
â 
But don't feel guilty, because Science says that far from being a mark of boredom or fatigue, yawning might help your brain cool off. Literally.â 
â 
âœ”ï¸A study led by Andrew Gallup showed that yawning frequency varies with the season and that people are less likely to yawn when the heat outdoors exceeds body temperature. In a few words, yawning can serve as a method for regulating brain temperature.â 
âœ”ï¸The scientists found that participants were more likely to yawn in the winter than in the summer when ambient temperatures were equal to or exceeding body temperature. They concluded that warmer temperatures provide no relief for overheated brains, which, according to the thermoregulatory theory of yawning, stay cool via a heat exchange with the air drawn in during a yawn.â 
â 
ğŸ˜„ So keep calm, and yawn in peace! ğŸ˜â 
â

Eat balanced breakfast!

If there is anything worse than being stressed, itâ€™s being stressed AND hungry! To prevent you from getting hangry hours before lunch, weâ€™re going to show you how to build a balanced breakfast.

The key things you want to focus on for breakfast are: protein, carbs, fat, fiber, and some color from fruits or veggies. Nut butters (are you team almond butter or PB??) provide protein and healthy fats, oats and other whole grains give you carbs and fiber, and eggs and yogurt are good sources of protein. Here are some of our favorite breakfast combos:

- Whole wheat toast or @vansfood waffles topped with nut butter (@sunbutter or @crazyrichardspb) and a side of fruit 
- @siggisdairy yogurt with granola (@purely_elizabeth or @kindsnacks), fruit, and nut butter 
- Overnight oats topped with fruit and nuts 
- Scrambled eggs (try @justegg101 for a delicious plant-based egg option!) with potatoes and veggies

â€¢Berries & Cream Yogurtâ€¢
This is my go to Saturday morning breakfast. Saturdayâ€™s are a busy day for me at the gym, so I need a meal that is going to fill me up and fuel my body. 
...
Ingredients:
â€¢1/2 cup quick oats 
â€¢1 cup water (you could use milk too!)
â€¢2 tsps peanut butter 
â€¢1/2 tsp cinnamon 
â€¢20g vanilla protein powder (I used @1stphorm Level 1) 
â€¢170g nonfat greek yogurt 
â€¢1/2 cup berries of your choice (I used blackberries and raspberries) 
â€¢1/2 tbsp honey for drizzling 
....
1. Prepare the oatmeal on the stove or microwave (oats, water, cinnamon & pb). I like to add in the pb while itâ€™s cooking to help thicken up the oatmeal. 
2. Once cooked, stir in the protein powder
3. Top oatmeal with yogurt 
4. Add on berries and drizzle some honey over the top! 
...
You can easily adjust the amount of oats for higher carbs, or add addition protein powder or yogurt for more protein. 
My macros for this meal were: 
30P/10F/55C 
I am eating this before a workout so I want to keep my protein and carbs high but my fat low! 
Try this out next time you need a pre-workout breakfast! ğŸ’ª
